	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99517212350302><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Some general questions</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jul 15th 12:42 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, first of all, this is my first time playing EQ. I read the instruction booklet and decided that I liked the the monk class most. I thought I should come here first, however, before I made my character so I wouldn't regret a bad decision later. First of all, I decided on an Iksar for my race. I don't like the evil aspect very much but I simply can't resist the advantages that the lizards have over the humans. Now, I heard from a friend that all the classes have epic wepon quests. What is the epic for a monk? I need to know so that I can prepare for it by practicing the weapon skill it requires. I want to be ready. Also, I heard that monks mostly wear light armor such as silk and cloth. Is it worth the time and effort to train tailoring so that I can make these armors? I've read a few posts about tailoring and some say it was easy, yet others say it was a nightmare. I'm guessing it is mostly based on how much patience you have. If it is a waste of time though, I would like to know. Finaly, what skills should I put points into? I am planning on RP'ing this monk, so I may put most of my start points into agility and dexterity to get an "historicaly acurate" monk. I may also train no other weapon skill besides hand-to-hand as monks are supposed to be masters of martial arts, not club wielding. However, if I need some other skill for my epic or if this is simply a bad idea I would appreciate any advice as to how I should make this character. Thanks in advance.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
