	   <tr><td colspan=2>Aye, I am human, and it's good to look to people with Iksar monk experience for advice in the ways of the leezards.&nbsp;&nbsp;Kensuke and Niteklaw covered pretty much everything you need to know for your first 15-20 levels.<br><br>Just a comment about tailoring.<br><br>It sucks.<br><br>I took up tailoring with the 'role-play' aspect in mind - I refuse to buy raw materials from other players.  Because of this, i either have to hunt spiders or pray that somebody sold silks to a merchant here and there.  I've spent a LOT of time at this - time that could have been devoted to leveling - and my skill is a whopping 40.  I just did 15 combines the other day - skill didn't budge.  I was warned that it's possibly the toughest skill to master, and it appears to be true.<br><br>Now, they just made a change that makes life MUCH easier for tailoring monks.  Spiderling and spider silks stack now, so you can actually accumulate them without having to lug a sewing kit around.  Many PC's pay good money for silk, silk threads, and silk swatches.  On Druzzil Ro, i typically see swatches (two spider silks combined - never fails) going for 2pp each.  Not sure about the threads (two spiderling silks) but they're worth money too.  So, if ya want to make some cash - just loot and stack up the silks, put a sewing kit in the bank, combine them, and sell the stacks for good pp.<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 49th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro <br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
