	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'll add a few comments:<br><br>1) Yes, Iksar are disliked by all others but this CAN be remidied. Do NOT let this discourage you.<br>2) As for point allocation on startup, put 5-10 points in strength and the rest in AGI when you're an Iksar. Most human monks will want to boost their STA some, but this isn't critical to us Lizzards.<br>3) Always keep all of your weapon skills up. There is a cap at each level determining how far you can go up, and you will thank yourself if you keep all three (1hb, 2hb, h2h) up from day one.<br>4) Train ALL you special skills. Monks get a lot of them and become a more versatile character if you have all of them available to you. You should specifically be sure to hit the 'Mend'-special skill as soon as it cycles for the first 10-12 levels. It won't matter as you will rarely succeed in using the skill at first, but there is a chance it will go up each time you use it.<br>5) Always stay light-weight if you can (below 14 wt.)<br>6) As for tailoring, don't worry about training it to make armor for yourself. Spend that time levelling and getting money. If you want to train tailoring, do so only if you are planning to make a career of it. Yes, you can get to a point where you can make Raw Silk for yourself (that's the bit people call easy), but if you want to really go places with your craft you will need to work EXCEEDINGLY hard. Tailoring is THE most dificult trade to master (I said dificult, not expensive).<br>7) If you're serious about playing a monk to his fullest potential, keep checking this forum. People like Keyeluke, Kensuko and Osano are always ready to help out. Just remember that they are (as far as I know) all HUMAN monks, at there is a VERY big difference in the playing style and often in the equipment choice of these two races.<br><br>Have fun and Welcome to Norrath!<br><br>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka<br>Iksar Monk, Povar-Tarew Artisans, Xev server.<br>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://www.povartarewalliance.org/roster/index.shtml?action=preview&charname=Niteklaw&showAlts=false target=_new><b>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka</b></a><br>Brother of the Celestial Fists<br>Povar Tarew Alliance, Xev</td></tr>
